## Description {#details}

A linked-list with a custom, local allocator.

Expose a std::list-like interface that owns and uses a custom LLVM-style allocator (e.g., <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8e612822d4ba7bb36c9c79582a567108">BumpPtrAllocator</a>), leveraging <em><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/simple-ilist">simple&#95;ilist</a></em> for the implementation details.

Because this list owns the allocator, calling <em>splice()</em> with a different list isn&#39;t generally safe. As such, <em>splice</em> has been left out of the interface entirely.

Definition at line 33 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/allocatorlist-h">AllocatorList.h</a>.
